/*! 
 * \page solvers Sensor Placement Solvers


The SPOT sensor placement solvers are launched with the \ref spExecutable "sp" python script.
Command-line options for \c sp
can specify any of a set of performance/cost goals as the objective
to be optimized, as well as constraints on performance/cost goals.
The problem formulation that is solved by the sensor placement solvers
is described 
in Section
\ref formulations.

The \c sp executable currently interfaces with 
integer programming (IP) solvers, a GRASP multi-start
local search heuristic, and a Lagrangian heuristic.
The IP formulation can be used to find globally 
optimal solutions.  The GRASP heuristic has proven effective at 
finding optimal solutions to a variety of large-scale applications.
Finally, the Lagrangian heuristic finds near-optimal solutions while
computing a lower bound on the best possible solution.  The following table highlights the capabilities of these solvers, and in particular their 
ability to support advanced features in SPOT:

\htmlonly
<center>
\endhtmlonly
<table>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="lightgray" align="left"><b>Solver Feature</b></td>
<td bgcolor="lightgray" align="center"><b>IP</b></td>
<td bgcolor="lightgray" align="center"><b>GRASP</b></td>
<td bgcolor="lightgray" align="center"><b>Lagrangian</b></td>
</tr>

<tr>
