The following sections provide examples that illustrate the use of the \c sp script, and the
different features of these solvers.  These examples can be run in the
\c spot/examples/simple directory.  We assume that \c IMPACT files have been generated
with the following commands:
\verbatim
    tevasim -tsg Net3.tsg -tso Net3.tso Net3.inp Net3.out
    tso2Impact Net3 Net3.tso -mc -vc -td -nfd -ec -epanetin Net3.inp
\endverbatim



\section solvers2 A Simple Example

The following example minimizes the extent of contamination (ec)
while limiting the number of sensors (ns) to no more than 5.  The PICO
solver is used to solve this problem.

\verbatim
../../bin/sp --path=../../bin --path=../../etc/mod --network=Net3 --objective=ec
	--ub=ns,5 --solver=pico

read_impact_files:  /home/wehart/src/spot-limited/examples/simple/Net3_ec.impact

Number of Nodes                :  97
Number of Contamination Impacts: 9458

Running PICO...
../../bin/PICO --debug=1 --lpType=clp   --tableInitFrac=0.05 --RRTrialsPerCall=8
	--RRDepthThreshold=-1 --usingCuts=true  Net3.mod
	/home/wehart/src/spot-limited/examples/simple/Net3.dat
... PICO done
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Sensor placement id:        22971
Number of sensors:          5
Total cost:                 0
Sensor node IDs:            19 28 54 63 75
Sensor junctions:           119 141 193 207 239

Impact File:                Net3_ec.impact
Number of events:           236
Min impact:                 0.0000
Mean impact:                8478.9674
Lower quartile impact:      0.0000
Median impact:              6949.0000
Upper quartile impact:      12530.0000
Value at Risk (VaR) (  5%): 25960.0000
TCE                 (  5%): 33323.2833
Max impact:                 42994.8000
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Greedy ordering of sensors
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
54      29124.8004
19      18687.7292
63      11471.6750
75      9951.8699
28      8478.9674
Done with sp
\endverbatim

The summary information (beginning with "Sensor placement id:") is generated by \ref evalsensorExecutable "evalsensor".  This summary describes the sensor placement
and the performance of this sensor placement with respect to the impact measure that was minimized.
In addition to the mean performance, various other statistics are included:
<ul>

<li> <b>min</b> - The minimum impact over all contamination events.
If we make the 
assumption that a sensor protects the node at which it is placed, then this
measure will generally be zero.

<li> <b>mean</b> - The mean (or average) impact over all contamination events.

<li> <b>lower quartile</b> - 25% of contamination events,
weighted by their likelihood, have an impact value less than this quartile.

<li> <b>median</b> - 50% of contamination events,
weighted by their likelihood, have an impact value less than this quartile.

<li> <b>upper quartile</b> - 75% of contamination events,
weighted by their likelihood, have an impact value less than this quartile.

<li> <b>VaR</b> - The value at risk (VaR) uses a user-defined quantile: alpha.
100*alpha% of contamination events,
weighted by their likelihood, have an impact value less than this quantile.

<li> <b>TCE</b> - The tailed-conditioned expectation (TCE) is the mean value
of the impacts that are greater than or equal to VaR.

<li> <b>worst</b> - The value of the worst impact.

</ul>
A greedy sensor placement is described by \c evalsensor, which takes
the five sensor placements and places them one-at-a-time, minimizing
the impact as each sensor is placed.  This gives a sense of the relative
priorities for these sensors.

The following example shows how to solve this same problem with the GRASP heuristic.  This solver finds the same (optimal) solution as the IP solver, though much more quickly.

\verbatim
../../bin/sp --path=../../bin --network=Net3 --objective=ec --ub=ns,5
	--solver=heuristic

read_impact_files:  /home/wehart/src/spot-limited/examples/simple/Net3_ec.impact
Note: witness aggregation disabled for heuristic

Number of Nodes                :  97
Number of Contamination Impacts: 9458

Number of sensors=5
