\section solvers2c Fixing Sensor Placement Locations

Properties of the sensor locations can be specified with the
\c --sensor-locations option.  This options specifies a \ref locationsFile
that can control whether sensor locations are feasible or infeasible, and
fixed or unfixed.  For example, suppose the file \c locations contains
\verbatim
infeasible 193 119 141 207 239
fixed 161
\endverbatim
The following example shows how these restrictions impact the solution.  Compared to the 
first example above, we have a less-optimal solution, since we cannot use the sensor locations above, and since
we are required to include junction \c 161.

\verbatim
../../bin/sp --path=../../bin --path=../../etc/mod --network=Net3 --objective=ec
	--ub=ns,5 --solver=pico --sensor-locations=locations

